                            <comment id="200023" author="sarah" created="Thu, 22 Jun 2017 19:05:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The version check is in master code, not sure why the test wasn&apos;t skipped.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="194436" author="bobijam" created="Thu, 4 May 2017 13:13:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s an interop test issue. but the strange thing is the MDS Lustre version of the test in this ticket is 2.9.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but conf_sanity test_87 has the version test&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;test_87() { #LU-6544
        [[ $(lustre_version_code $SINGLEMDS1) -ge $(version_code 2.9.51) ]] ||
                { skip &quot;Need MDS version at least 2.9.51&quot; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; return; }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And the test should be skipped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you take a look at the client&apos;s conf-sanity.sh test script to see whether the version check is there or not?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
